To connect AWS to on-premises?

| Scenario                | Solution                  |
| ----------------------- | ------------------------- |
| Single VPC + On-prem    | Simple Site-to-Site VPN   |
| Multiple VPCs + On-prem | Transit Gateway ✅         |
| Multi-region + On-prem  | Transit Gateway peering ✅ |


How to setup Site-to-Site VPN:

# 1. Create Virtual Private Gateway (AWS side)

VPC → Virtual Private Gateways → Create Virtual Private Gateway
  → Name: my-vgw
  → ASN: Amazon default ASN
  → Create
  
Then:
  → Select VGW → Actions → Attach to VPC → Select your VPC ✅

# 2. Create Customer Gateway (On-prem router IP)

VPC → Customer Gateways → Create Customer Gateway
  → Name: my-cgw
  → BGP ASN: 65000 (on-prem router ASN)
  → IP Address: <your on-prem router public IP>
  → Create ✅

On-Premises                    AWS
┌──────────────┐               ┌──────────────┐
│ Router       │               │ VGW          │
│ 203.0.113.10 │←── VPN ──────│              │
│ (CGW in AWS) │               │              │
└──────────────┘               └──────────────┘

# 3. Create VPN Connection between them

VPC → Site-to-Site VPN Connections → Create VPN Connection
  → Name: my-vpn
  → Virtual Private Gateway: select my-vgw
  → Customer Gateway: Existing → select my-cgw
  → Routing: Static or Dynamic (BGP)
  → Static IP Prefix: 192.168.0.0/24  (on-prem CIDR)
  → Create ✅

# 4. Download config → apply on on-prem router
# 5. Update route tables in VPC
